Description: A comprehensive toolkit for analyzing interpersonal and
    behavioral synchrony in continuous time series data. Provides highly
    efficient, C++ backed implementations of windowed cross-correlation
    (WCC) and peak-picking algorithms to quantify nonstationary lead-lag
    relationships. Includes a complete preprocessing pipeline for
    behavioral data featuring zero-phase smoothing, time-bin aggregation,
    and kinematic velocity and speed calculations. Additionally, the
    package supports rigorous null-hypothesis testing through
    circular-shift surrogate data generation (pseudo-synchrony analysis)
    to distinguish genuine interaction from spurious correlation.
